1+x)^(1/x)<br />\n<br />\nLim x-&gt;0 (1/x)-&gt;無限大<br />\nLim x-&gt;0 (1+x)=1<br />\nLim x-&gt;0 (1+x)^(1/x)=1<br />\n利申 讀緊幼稚園"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-13T17:29:45.000Z","msg":"想問下點解後者不同意？ 我用電腦計佢話0/x=0 x-&gt;0<br />\n因為x 並非真係0 <br />\n由於份母唔係0 , 0 除乜都係0"},{"pid":"a67c28c000264496d834c37a580e706b3d9afc7e","tid":1312597,"uid":61827,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"cb05f0cffef58fe9dca06e714d84e2a945f05130","tid":1312597,"uid":249885,"like":0,"dislike":3,"score":-3,"quote":{"pid":"7116ec6060c2f7b30804d89099f4564257365819","tid":1312597,"uid":130568,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-07-13T16:55:14.000Z","msg":"本身就成舊數take limit<br />\n你就將過limit 淨係apply 響(1+x)^(1/x) <br />\n點解你會覺得可以咁做?"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-07-13T17:24:49.000Z","msg":"你是否同意<br />\n0/x=0 when x-&gt;0<br />\n<br />\n如同意<br />\n你應該同意（e-e)/x=0 when x-&gt;0<br />\n<br />\n由於lim x-&gt;0 (1+x)^(1/x)=e  <br />\n故題目lim x-&gt;0 和 (e-e)/x 一樣<br />\n<br />\n但計出嚟嘅答案錯 其實係咪引證 lim x-&gt;0 (1+x)^(1/x) 並非exactly = e ?????"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-13T17:40:07.000Z","msg":"計出來的答案錯 是因為lim x-&gt;0 (1+x)^(1/x)=e 不足以推論出 lim [(1+x)^(1/x)-e]/x = lim (e-e)/x<br />\n<br />\n例如 由於 lim x-&gt;0 x=0<br />\n但 lim x-&gt;0 x/x 不等於 lim x-&gt;0 0/x=0"},{"pid":"12acaa9af128b6c562849f14f6ec709a38e1c5f1","tid":1312597,"uid":11890,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-13T17:49:17.000Z","msg":"The rule for taking limit of a quotient says<br />\nlim f(x)/g(x) = lim f(x) / lim g(x) provided that lim f(x) and lim g(x) both exist and <strong><span style=\"color: red;\">lim g(x) &ne; 0</span></strong>.<br />\n<br />\nIn your case lim [ (1+x)^(1/x) - e ] / x,<br />\nthe demonimator function x has limit 0, so you can't tell the limit by just claiming the numerator function (1+x)^(1/x) - e has limit 0."}]}